 The equation $x^2-y^2=47$ can be rewritten as $(x+y)(x-y)=47$ . Since 47 is a prime number, its only positive factorization is $47=47\cdot1$ .  Thus, we have the systems of equations \begin{align*}
x+y&=47,\\
x-y&=1,  
\end{align*}or \begin{align*}
x+y&=-47,\\
x-y&=-1,  
\end{align*}or \begin{align*}
x+y&=1,\\
x-y&=47,  
\end{align*}and \begin{align*}
x+y&=-1,\\
x-y&=-47.
\end{align*}The first and third systems have the positive solutions $x=24$ , $y=23$  and $x=24$ , $y=-23$ , respectively; the other two systems have the negative solutions after solving.  Therefore, there are 4 solutions.  <answer> 4 </answer>

