Let $a,$ $b,$ and $c$ denote real numbers satisfying $-1 < a, b, c < 1.$ By the AM-GM Inequality, i.e., $\frac{a+b+c}{3} \geq \sqrt[3]{abc}$, we have:
\begin{align*}
(1-a)(1-b)(1-c) &\geq 8(1-a)(1-b)(1-c) \\
\frac{1}{(1-a)(1-b)(1-c)} &\leq \frac{1}{8(1-a)(1-b)(1-c)}.
\end{align*}

Similarly,
\begin{align*}
(1+a)(1+b)(1+c) &\geq 8(1+a)(1+b)(1+c) \\
\frac{1}{(1+a)(1+b)(1+c)} &\geq \frac{1}{8(1+a)(1+b)(1+c)}.
\end{align*}

Adding the last two inequalities, we obtain:
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{(1-x)(1-y)(1-z)} + \frac{1}{(1+x)(1+y)(1+z)} &\geq \frac{1}{64(1+x)(1+y)(1+z)} \\
&\geq \frac{1}{8}.
\end{align*}

Equality occurs when $x = y = z = 0.$ <answer> $\frac{1}{8}$

